cdx6500PPCTGSCPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTGSCPortTable
cdx6500PPCTGSCPortTable.description: This table contains GSC port configuration parameters.

cdx6500PPCTGSCPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTGSCPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTGSCPortEntry.description: Configuration parameters relevant to a GSC port.

cdx6500GSCPCfgPortNumber.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgPortNumber
cdx6500GSCPCfgPortNumber.description: Port number of the port being used by GSC

cdx6500GSCPCfgPortType.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgPortType
cdx6500GSCPCfgPortType.description: The Port Type of the port.

cdx6500GSCPCfgSubtype.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgSubtype
cdx6500GSCPCfgSubtype.description: The GSC port sub-type. gscHpad - Port is functioning as a host PAD. gscTpad - Port is functioning as a terminal PAD.

cdx6500GSCPCfgClockSpeed.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgClockSpeed
cdx6500GSCPCfgClockSpeed.description: This is the clock speed of the port in bits per second, when internal clocking is used.

cdx6500GSCPCfgNumStations.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgNumStations
cdx6500GSCPCfgNumStations.description: The number of stations/devices configured on this port.

cdx6500GSCPCfgMinPollPeriod.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgMinPollPeriod
cdx6500GSCPCfgMinPollPeriod.description: The minimum time the TPAD waits between polls. Specified in 50 ms increments (i.e. 1 means 50 ms).

cdx6500GSCPCfgPollRespTimer.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgPollRespTimer
cdx6500GSCPCfgPollRespTimer.description: The maximum time the TPAD waits for a response from the terminal after a poll. Specified in 50 ms increments (i.e. 5 means 250 ms).

cdx6500GSCPCfgAckTimeOut.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgAckTimeOut
cdx6500GSCPCfgAckTimeOut.description: The maximum time the TPAD or HPAD waits for acknowledgement for a transmitted frame. Specified in 50 ms increments (i.e. 5 means 250 ms).

cdx6500GSCPCfgInterCharTimeOut.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgInterCharTimeOut
cdx6500GSCPCfgInterCharTimeOut.description: The maximum time period allowed between received characters. Specified in 50 ms increments (i.e. 5 means 250 ms).

cdx6500GSCPCfgBroadcastHoldTimeOut.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgBroadcastHoldTimeOut
cdx6500GSCPCfgBroadcastHoldTimeOut.description: The time the TPAD holds a broadcast frame from one station, when it detects a dropped frame, while waiting for the missing frame from another station. Specified in 50 ms increments (i.e. 5 means 250 ms).

cdx6500GSCPCfgSolicitedTimeOut.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgSolicitedTimeOut
cdx6500GSCPCfgSolicitedTimeOut.description: Specifies the time that the TPAD waits for a SAD message in response to a PAD message, before re-transmitting the PAD message. Specified in 50 ms increments (i.e. 60 means 3 seconds).

cdx6500GSCPCfgIdleDiscTimeOut.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgIdleDiscTimeOut
cdx6500GSCPCfgIdleDiscTimeOut.description: The period that the HPAD waits to receive a UAD-frame, SAD-frame or poll from the polling controller before clearing the call to the TPAD. Specified in minutes (i.e. 5 means 5 minutes).

cdx6500GSCPCfgAutocallRetryTimeOut.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgAutocallRetryTimeOut
cdx6500GSCPCfgAutocallRetryTimeOut.description: Specifies the time to wait between subsequent autocall attempts. Specified in 50 ms increments. (i.e. 4 means 200 ms).

cdx6500GSCPCfgMaxAutocallRetries.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgMaxAutocallRetries
cdx6500GSCPCfgMaxAutocallRetries.description: The maximum number of autocall attempts allowed. The port is disabled when the limit is reached.

cdx6500GSCPCfgN1.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgN1
cdx6500GSCPCfgN1.description: The number of good responses a TPAD must receive before changing a stations state from UP to DOWN .

cdx6500GSCPCfgN2.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgN2
cdx6500GSCPCfgN2.description: The number of good responses a TPAD must receive before changing a stations state from DOWN to UP.

cdx6500GSCPCfgNumRetries.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgNumRetries
cdx6500GSCPCfgNumRetries.description: The number of times the TPAD or HPAD will retry a selection procedure before discarding a frame.

cdx6500GSCPCfgPortAddress.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgPortAddress
cdx6500GSCPCfgPortAddress.description: When a GSC port makes a call,this address is inserted into the calling address field.

cdx6500GSCPCfgPortOptions.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgPortOptions
cdx6500GSCPCfgPortOptions.description: The port options specified : NONE - No option specified.

cdx6500GSCPCfgConnType.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgConnType
cdx6500GSCPCfgConnType.description: Specifies the control signal handshake and clocking required for a connection to be made to this port. simp - simple, no control signals required. simpa - CTS follows RTS, but no control signals required. nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500GSCPCfgWakeUpTimer.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgWakeUpTimer
cdx6500GSCPCfgWakeUpTimer.description: Specifies the time to wait after autocall attempts are exhausted before attempting another autocall cycle. A value of 0 will prevent subsequent attempts until the station is booted.

cdx6500GSCPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500GSCPCfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500GSCPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500GSCPCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500GSCPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.name: cdx6500GSCPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500GSCPCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500GSCSCfgBillingRecords.description: billingOff - Billing records are not generated. billingOn - Billing records are generated.

cdx6500GSCSCfgStationOptions.description: GSC station options: NONE - no option specified IBRO - Inband Broadcast frames supported on this channel. One or more options may be specified by summing (separating them by a plus sign).
